LlmFixer
/ Planner produced invalid output — retry with the prior conversation cached
/ (system prompt + goal already in context; only the correction message is new).
/ The error message is sharp enough that the LLM corrects rather than anchors.

- call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="planner-validation-failed", errorMessage=%!error.Message%
- set %fixerMessages% = [{"Role":"user", "Content":"Your previous response was rejected: %!error.Message%\n\nReturn the corrected plan. Each step's `actions` MUST be a non-empty array of `\"module.action\"` strings from the catalog (e.g. `\"variable.set\"`, `\"file.read\"`). `index` is 0-based."}], type=json
- llm.query Messages=%fixerMessages%, Schema={description: string, steps: [{index: int, actions: [string], confidence: string, explanation?: string}]}, cache=%!build.cache%, previousConversation=%plan%, write to %plan%

/ Don't recurse into Validate here — the runtime retries QueryAndValidatePlan
/ (the wrapped call), which calls Validate itself. Validate-call inside this
/ fixer would create a second loop with no bound.
